### Rule ID : CUR-001
## Title : Track Feature Implementation Lifecycle

## Description :
Ensure all implemented features are documented in cursorRule/ModificationsImplemented.md and removed from cursorRule/HowToImproveCurrentFeatures.md to maintain accurate codebase records 

## Trigger :
Feature implementation commit detected in version control.

## Conditions :
1. The feature exists in cursorRule/HowToImproveCurrentFeatures.md under "Small Features to Implement" 
2. Code changes match the feature's implementation criteria.

## Actions :
1. Remove Entry : Delete the feature's description from cursorRule/HowToImproveCurrentFeatures.md.
2. Log Modification : Add a new entry to cursorRule/ModificationsImplemented.md with:
 (a) Feature name
 (b) Implementation date
 (c)Author/PR reference
 (d)Brief impact summary 

## Validation : Verify no duplicate entries exist in either file.
#Example :
```
# Before (HowToImproveCurrentFeatures.md)
- [ ] Add dark mode toggle (src/ui/theme.js)  

# After (ModificationsImplemented.md)
- 2025-04-11: Dark mode toggle implemented by @user (PR #123)  
  - Impact: Improved accessibility, 15% reduced screen glare
```  
##References :
- Codebase documentation standards 
- Continuous integration best practices 
- AI-assisted codebase tracking 

##Notes :
- Use git blame or AI tools like Archie to verify feature origins.
- Automate via pre-commit hooks for enforcement 